,
"en"
:
"The endlessh module is a wrapper module based on Docker that provides quick startup and management capabilities for endlessh-go.\nendlessh-go (https://github.com/shizunge/endlessh-go) is a honeypot tool implemented in Go. It inherits the powerful features of endlessh, such as delaying responses to put malicious scanning tools or automated attack scripts in a suspended state, thus consuming the attacker's time and resources.\nUnlike endlessh, it can export Prometheus metrics and Grafana dashboards, providing users with a more intuitive visualization of attack sources (users who need to use the visual dashboard can find detailed instructions in the endlessh-go Github repository).\n"
}
,
