,
"cn"
:
"输出或处理数字序列"
}
,
"#desc"
:
{
"en"
:
"Generate number sequences, same functionality as GNU seq, but with a compact colon-separated range syntax (`start:step:end`) and the ability to invoke shell commands or inject functions for each element.\n\nDifferences from GNU seq:\n- Uses `:` as range separator — `x seq 1:10` instead of `seq 1 10`\n- Supports shell invocation — pass a shell expression, `eval` command, or function name to process each number\n- Supports awk inline code — write `{ ... }` to use awk for iteration and processing\n- Pure shell loop by default — no external process overhead, ideal for small ranges\n"
,
"cn"
:
"生成数字序列，功能与 GNU seq 相同，但采用紧凑的冒号分隔范围语法（`start:step:end`），并支持对每个元素调用 shell 命令或注入函数。\n\n与 GNU seq 的差异：\n- 使用 `:` 作为范围分隔符——`x seq 1:10` 代替 `seq 1 10`\n- 支持 shell 调用——传入 shell 表达式、`eval` 命令或函数名来处理每个数字\n- 支持 awk 内联代码——用 `{ ... }` 调用 awk 进行迭代和处理\n- 默认纯 shell 循环——无外部进程开销，适合小范围数据\n"
}
,
"$ref"
:
"x-advise://seq"
,
"#exec"
:
"xrc seq 2>/dev/null"
}
